---
title: "AppScan Custom Dashboard — Multi-Data-Source Request Flow"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Browser
    participant FE as React SPA
    participant API as FastAPI /api/v1
    participant SEC as Security Layer
    participant MULTI as multi_endpoint
    participant SVC as AsocReadService
    participant ASOC as ASoC API (v4)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Note over U,DB: Request Flow — e.g. GET /api/v1/applications

    U->>FE: Navigate to Applications
    FE->>API: GET /api/v1/applications<br/>Authorization: Bearer JWT

    API->>SEC: get_current_user(JWT)
    SEC-->>API: UserContext(role, asset_group_ids)
    API->>SEC: assert_action_allowed("view_applications", role)
    SEC-->>API: Allowed

    API->>MULTI: aggregate_list("list_applications")

    Note over MULTI,ASOC: Parallel fetch from all enabled data sources

    MULTI->>DB: _load_sources() — fetch enabled endpoints
    DB-->>MULTI: [Source A, Source B]

    par Source A
        MULTI->>SVC: list_applications()
        SVC->>ASOC: GET /api/v4/Apps (Bearer token)
        ASOC-->>SVC: [App1, App2]
        SVC-->>MULTI: tagged with _data_source_id
    and Source B
        MULTI->>SVC: list_applications()
        SVC->>ASOC: GET /api/v4/Apps (Bearer token)
        ASOC-->>SVC: [App3]
        SVC-->>MULTI: tagged with _data_source_id
    end

    MULTI-->>API: merged [App1, App2, App3]

    API->>SEC: filter_by_asset_group(apps, user)
    SEC-->>API: filtered apps (role-scoped)

    API-->>FE: 200 OK [filtered apps]
    FE-->>U: Render application list
